### SYSTEM 3: GRAZE SYSTEM

When a bullet passes within 6px of the UFO center (but doesn't hit the 4px hitbox), it counts as a "graze":

Add to game state variables:
```javascript
let grazeMultiplier = 1.0;
let grazeDecayRate = 0.03; // per second
let grazeCount = 0;
let grazeFlashTimer = 0;
```

In `updateProjectiles`, after checking collision, check graze:
```javascript
// After hit check, if bullet didn't hit:
const dx = b.x - ufoCx;
const dy = b.y - ufoCy;
const dist = Math.sqrt(dx*dx + dy*dy);
if (dist < 12 && dist > 4 && !b.grazed) {
  b.grazed = true; // only graze once per bullet
  grazeCount++;
  grazeMultiplier = Math.min(grazeMultiplier + 0.1, 5.0);
  grazeFlashTimer = 0.1;
  // Spawn graze spark particle
  spawnParticle(b.x, b.y, (Math.random()-0.5)*60, (Math.random()-0.5)*60, '#ffffff', 0.3, 1);
  AudioManager.playGraze(); // we'll add this
}
```

In the main update, decay the multiplier:
```javascript
grazeMultiplier = Math.max(1.0, grazeMultiplier - grazeDecayRate * dt);
```

Multiply ALL score gains by `grazeMultiplier`. Display it on the HUD.

Add `playGraze()` to audio.js: a short, ascending ping sound (higher pitch as multiplier climbs). Use a quick sine oscillator at frequency `400 + grazeMultiplier * 100`, duration 0.05s.

