### SYSTEM 5: BULLET CANCEL ON COW COLLECTION

When a cow is successfully abducted (collected), cancel all bullets within a radius and convert them to score pickups:

```javascript
const CANCEL_BASE_RADIUS = 40;

function bulletCancel(cx, cy, combo) {
  const radius = CANCEL_BASE_RADIUS + combo * 8; // scales with combo
  let cancelled = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < BULLET_POOL_SIZE; i++) {
    const b = bulletPool[i];
    if (!b.alive) continue;
    const dx = b.x - cx;
    const dy = b.y - cy;
    if (dx*dx + dy*dy < radius * radius) {
      // Convert to score pickup particle
      spawnScorePickup(b.x, b.y, 10); // 10 points each
      killBullet(b);
      cancelled++;
    }
  }
  if (cancelled > 5) {
    // Big cancel flash
    screenShake = Math.min(screenShake + cancelled * 0.3, 8);
    // Ring shockwave particle
    // Play cancel sound
    AudioManager.playBulletCancel();
  }
  return cancelled;
}
```

You'll need to add a `spawnScorePickup` function that creates small floating point-value particles that drift toward the UFO and auto-collect. These are simple particles with a `scoreValue` property that get added to score when they touch the UFO.

Add `playBulletCancel()` to audio.js: a satisfying "whoooosh" sweep sound. Use a noise burst with a bandpass filter that sweeps from 2000Hz down to 200Hz over 0.3s.

Call `bulletCancel(cow.x, cow.y, comboCount)` right after a cow is collected in the combo/scoring section.

